  "title": "Assistant Engineer Flat Optics and Photonics Integration (APM), (NSTIC), IME",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for an <strong>Assistant Engineer</strong> to support the <strong>Flat Optics and Photonics Integration</strong> development. This is an exciting opportunity for an early-career engineer to gain hands-on experience in semiconductor processing and work on cutting-edge flat optics/photonics technologies.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Assist in process development and fabrication of semiconductor device. </li><li>Perform cleanroom equipment (e.g. metrology) and lot operation. </li><li>Perform process characterization, data collection and analysis. </li><li>Work with engineers to troubleshoot fabrication issues and optimize process flows.</li><li>Document process parameters and contribute to process development reports.</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma in Electrical Engineering, Applied Science or Semiconductor related field.</li><li>Hands-on experience (2-3 years) in semiconductor processing or fabrication. </li><li>Able to work in clean room environment is a MUST. </li><li>Basic knowledge of semiconductor materials. </li><li>Ability to work in a fast-paced, collaborative environment. </li><li>Prior internship or working experience in semiconductor fabrication.</li></ul><p><strong>The above eligibility criteria are not exhaustive. A*STAR may include additional selection criteria based on its prevailing recruitment policies. These policies may be amended from time to time without notice. We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</strong></p>",
